{"to":["sarah.thompson@cch.org"],"subject":"Project Update: HEAP & Vax4All","body":"Hi Sarah,

I wanted to share a quick status update on our two active initiatives:

1. Health Empowerment and Awareness Program (HEAP)
   • Content: Draft curriculum for the educational workshops is 80% complete. Pamphlet designs have been sent to the comms team for final graphic polish.
   • Next steps (this week):
       – Finalize the workshop curriculum and upload it to the shared drive.
       – Confirm venue availability for the first session (target: June 5).
       – Begin recording the short video segments for the web resources.

2. Vax4All Vaccination Drive
   • Content: Temporary vaccination site locations in Oakwood Village have been shortlisted (community center, public library lot, and Riverside Park pop-up).
   • Coordination: Local healthcare providers have tentatively agreed to staff two of the three sites.
   • Next steps (this week):
       – Secure written confirmations from providers.
       – Finalize volunteer orientation materials and schedule a training call for Thursday.
       – Send out the first batch of outreach emails/social posts once comms signs off on graphics.

Let me know if you see any gaps or if there’s anything else you’d like me to tackle.

Best,
John","cc":null,"bcc":null,"execution_log_path":"data/logs/item91_execution_log.json"}
